Class simzombie.engine.Parameters extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

serialVersionUID: 1L

Serialized Fields

environment

Environment environment
All simulations store an environment in their parameters, for easy access

loggingEnabled

boolean loggingEnabled
If true, simulations are logged so they can be saved or replayed. If this behaviour is not desirable, setting this to false will run simulations with significantly less ram usage

displayGraphics

boolean displayGraphics
If true, graphics are displayed initially

displayGraph

boolean displayGraph
If true, the graph is displayed initially

stepDelay

int stepDelay
Number of milliseconds to pause between each step - usually only used for debugging purposes

timeStepping

boolean timeStepping
If this is true, the simulation pauses after each step. Usage is mainly for debugging.

population

int population
Initial TOTAL population of the simulation Any non-standard agents are subtracted from this total, for example a simulation with 5 Zombified agents will start with 5995 Susceptible and 5 Zombified agents

agentMaxSpeed

int agentMaxSpeed
Maximum speed of standard agents

agentMinSpeed

int agentMinSpeed
Minumum speed of standard agents

currentLunarPhase

int currentLunarPhase
Current lunar phase depicted in this simulation. While not strictly a parameter, this seemed like the most sensible place for this to be stored - arguably, it should be stored in some sort of Collection in the Simulation class, consider this later.

repeats

int repeats
Number of times the simulation repeats. This was partially implemented to average over a large number of simulation executions, but was never entirely completed. I believe MATLAB output is still created when repeats run, but there is no in-program support for graphing this

timeOfDay

Parameters.TimeOfDay timeOfDay
Current time of the day

monsterActiveDuringDay

boolean monsterActiveDuringDay
Whether monster agents are active during the day This should, strictly, be part of ZombieParameters, refactor later

monsterActiveDuringNight

boolean monsterActiveDuringNight
Whether monsters agents are active during the night This should, strictly, be part of ZombieParameters, refactor later

activeDuringLunarPhase

boolean[] activeDuringLunarPhase
Whether a monster is active during a specified lunar phase The index of the array corresponds to the integer for lunar phase. This should, strictly, be part of ZombieParameters, refactor later

name

java.lang.String name
Name of this specific simulation

chanceOfBirth

double chanceOfBirth
Chance of a natural birth occuring, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

chanceOfNaturalDeath

double chanceOfNaturalDeath
Chance of a natural death occuring, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

chanceOfNaturalInfection

double chanceOfNaturalInfection
Chance of a natural outbreak occuring, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

chanceASusceptibleWinsEncounter

double chanceASusceptibleWinsEncounter
Chance a susceptible successfully defeats a zombie in combat, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

chanceInfectionTransmits

double chanceInfectionTransmits
Chance an individual that falls victim to a zombie becomes a zombie, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

latencyPeriod

int latencyPeriod
Number of steps between becoming infected and becoming zombified

infectionRange

int infectionRange
The range at which zombies can interact with susceptibles, in pixels

int initialInfected
Number of infected individuals initially in the simulation

int initialZombified
Number of zombified individuals initially in the simulation

Minimum speed of susceptible agents

int susceptibleMaxSpeed
Maximum speed of susceptible agents

Minimum speed of zombified agents

int zombifiedMaxSpeed
Maximum speed of zombified agents

awarenessRaised

boolean awarenessRaised
This is toggled to true once awareness is raised - set to true for a simulation that begins aware

awarenessRaisedAt

double awarenessRaisedAt
Amount of the population that need to be affected before awareness is raised, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

awareChanceASusceptibleWinsEncounter

double awareChanceASusceptibleWinsEncounter
Chance a susceptible wins in combat against a zombie after awareness has been raised, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)

awareChanceInfectionTransmits

double awareChanceInfectionTransmits
Chance a susceptible that loses combat with a zombie becomes a zombie after awareness has been raised, represented as a percentage (1 is 1%, 0.1 is 0.001%)
